Class Student

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.Student
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public class Student
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class is responsible for modelling Student which details the attributes and methods of each Student object part of the STARS Planner system.

        userId - The userId of the Student object.

        nationality - The nationality of the Student object.

      • registerForCourse

        public void registerForCourse​(java.lang.String courseCodeToBeAdded,
                              IndexNumber indexNumberToBeAdded)
                       throws CourseRegisteredException,
                              ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException,
                              NoVacancyException,
                              CourseInWaitListException,
                              ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException,
                              MaxAuExceededException
        Registers a course for the Student and updating the TimeTable
        Parameters:
        courseCodeToBeAdded - The String representing the course code of the course to be added
        indexNumberToBeAdded - The IndexNumber of the course to be added
        Throws:
        CourseRegisteredException - if course is already registered
        CourseInWaitListException - if course is already in wait list
        NoVacancyException - if there are no more vacancies in the course
        ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException - if the new index number to be registered clashes with any of the already registered index numbers
        ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException - if the new index number to be registered clashes with any of the wait listed index numbers
        MaxAuExceededException - if Student has reached the maximum amount of AUs
        See Also:
        IndexNumber, TimeTable

      • swapIndexNumberWithPeer

        public void swapIndexNumberWithPeer​(java.lang.String courseCodeToBeSwapped,
                                    Student peer)
                             throws ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException,
                                    SameIndexNumberSwapException,
                                    ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException,
                                    PeerClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException,
                                    PeerClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException
        Swaps IndexNumber for a course with another Student and updating the TimeTable
        Parameters:
        courseCodeToBeSwapped - The String representing the course code of the IndexNumber to be swapped with peer
        peer - The Student in which this instance of Student is swapping the IndexNumber with
        Throws:
        SameIndexNumberSwapException - if the student and the peer has the same index number.
        ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException - if the peer's index number clashes with an index number that is in the student's wait list.
        PeerClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException - if the student's index number clashes with an index number that is in the peer's registered list.
        ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException - if the peer's index number clashes with an index number that is in the student's registered list.
        PeerClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException - if the student's index number clashes with an index number that is in the peer's wait list.
        See Also:
        Student, TimeTable

      • swapIndexNumber

        public void swapIndexNumber​(java.lang.String courseCodeToBeSwapped,
                            IndexNumber newIndexNumber)
                     throws ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException,
                            NoVacancySwapException,
                            SameIndexNumberSwapException,
                            ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException
        Swaps IndexNumber that is in Student object's TimeTable and updating the TimeTable
        Parameters:
        courseCodeToBeSwapped - The String representing the original course code of the IndexNumber to be swapped with
        newIndexNumber - The new IndexNumber to be swapped with the original
        Throws:
        ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException - if the new index number to be swapped clashes with any of the already registered index numbers
        ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException - if the new index number to be swapped clashes with any of the wait listed index numbers
        NoVacancySwapException - if there are no more vacancies in the new index number to be swapped to
        SameIndexNumberSwapException - if the pair of index numbers are the same
        See Also:
        IndexNumber, TimeTable

      • dropCourseAndRegisterNextStudentInWaitList

        public void dropCourseAndRegisterNextStudentInWaitList​(Course course,
                                                       IndexNumber indexNumberToBeDropped)
                                                throws CourseInWaitListException,
                                                       ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException,
                                                       CourseRegisteredException,
                                                       NoVacancyException,
                                                       ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException,
                                                       MaxAuExceededException
        Drops a Course from a Student and registers the front most Student in the wait list for that particular Course IndexNumber and updating the TimeTable. The exceptions can be ignored since the exceptions should have been taken care of when the index number is added into the student's wait list.
        Parameters:
        course - The Course to be dropped
        indexNumberToBeDropped - The IndexNumber of the course to be dropped
        Throws:
        CourseInWaitListException
        ClashingRegisteredIndexNumberException
        CourseRegisteredException
        NoVacancyException
        ClashingWaitListedIndexNumberException
        MaxAuExceededException
        See Also:
        IndexNumber, Course, TimeTable
